  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ utilizes QZ Tray integration for seamless printing without navigating print dialogs. This provides users with a one-click printing process for receipts, invoices, and labels directly to their assigned printer. Users can also create and customize print automation for a hands-free process for printing, further streamlining your ticket workflow.</p><p>Print Automation allows you to save time on printing documents by creating conditional triggers that automatically create print jobs, based on a ticket's status change. If you have not added print configurations for your location or run into any issues with automation, please see the previous steps of the Integrated Printing process.</p><h3 id=\"IntegratedPrinting104:CreatingandCustomizingPrintAutomation-PreviousSteps\">Previous Steps</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936949270/Integrated+Printing+103+Adding+and+Assigning+Printer+Configurations\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936949270\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Printing 103: Adding and Assigning Printer Configurations</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936457750/Integrated+Printing+102+Adding+Integrated+Printers\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936457750\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Printing 102: Adding Integrated Printers</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936359430/Integrated+Printing+101+Downloading+QZ+Tray\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936359430\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Printing 101: Downloading QZ Tray</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"IntegratedPrinting104:CreatingandCustomizingPrintAutomation-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936949301/Integrated+Printing+Troubleshooting\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936949301\" data-linked-resource-version=\"17\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Printing Troubleshooting</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933869057/Recommended+Hardware+Troubleshooting+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933869057\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Recommended Hardware Troubleshooting</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1932361958\" rel=\"nofollow\">Print Settings - Receipts</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933377656\" rel=\"nofollow\">Print Settings - Invoices</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182309.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"IntegratedPrinting104:CreatingandCustomizingPrintAutomation-CreatingandAssigningaPrintAutomation\">Creating and Assigning a Print Automation</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182315.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings Overview page, there is a list of Settings Categories on the left column. Click <strong>Integrated Printing </strong>to expand the options and select <strong>Print Automation</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182320.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Print Automation page, click <strong>Create Print Automation</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182326.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. Fill out the automation settings, based on which actions you would like to create a print job. Once you are satisfied with your selections, click <strong>Save</strong> to submit your changes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182338.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Name </strong>- Assign a name for your automation to identify your workflow. For example, \u201cTicket Close - Receipt.&quot;</p></li><li><p><strong>Description </strong>- Add a description of the automation for user reference.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location </strong>- Choose which location to assign this automation. Admins can select a single location or assign automation to all locations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Trigger </strong>- The default trigger for printing is when a ticket status changes.</p></li><li><p><strong>Condition </strong>- Select which ticket status(es) must be met to trigger the print job. Select any that you want to apply to the automation.</p></li><li><p><strong>Action </strong>- Select whether the trigger is activated when the ticket enters the assigned status or when it leaves the assigned status.</p></li><li><p><strong>Print Template </strong>- Choose whether this will print from the Ticket Receipt template, Ticket Invoice template, or Ticket Label template.</p></li><li><p><strong>Active </strong>- Toggle to activate/deactivate an automation.</p></li></ul><h2 id=\"IntegratedPrinting104:CreatingandCustomizingPrintAutomation-PrintAutomationonTickets\">Print Automation on Tickets</h2><p>To try out the new automation, create a new ticket, and save it into the status that you have selected for your automation. The print job(s) will be triggered automatically after the ticket is saved.</p><p /><p>A print job status window will appear, listing the print jobs in the queue and their current status.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182351.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Once everything has been printed, you will see <strong>Print job complete</strong> in the dialogue box for all jobs and the window will close in 3 seconds.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182401.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>If you need to make adjustments to your automation, go back to <strong>Location Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Integrated Printing</strong> \u2192 <strong>Print Automation </strong>and edit the automation by clicking on the <strong>Edit </strong>button on the right column under Actions.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936392218/image-20230608-182408.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
